                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d846">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.001H61/79: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Neville</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-13T18:00:00+09:00"
                            >August 13, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 13—5:52 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>167. The recent alleged disrespect of the Japanese Emperor at Seattle was
                    featured in the Japanese newspapers of August 10 and 12 but has not been
                    mentioned since the publication of a statement to the effect that Hornbeck
                    expressed to the Japanese Counselor a desire for local settlement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Neville</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
